Agnico Eagle has three active properties in Nunavut. The Meadowbank open-pit mine, in operation since 2010; the Amaruq satellite deposit, which is 50 kilometers northwest of Meadowbank and the Meliadine underground mine, in operation since 2019. To support the Nunavut projects, Agnico Eagle has staff based out of 2 regional offices, located in Val d’Or and Mirabel, Quebec.
YOUR NEXT CHALLENGE:

Reporting to Senior Coordinator Social Performance, the Database Administrator works in close collaboration with all members of the Nunavut Community Relations Department. He/she plays an important role in governance and database optimization, as well as ensuring data quality and analysis. The Database Administrator is in charge of database management, data reporting and data automation related to Community Relations projects and activities impacting or involving Kivalliq communities, groups or individuals. This role also supports project management activities.
Data
Analyze data quality from data sources to ensure accuracy in relation to a range of KPIs and requirements;
